==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bollard
<hw>Bol"lard</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Bole</er>
the stem of a tree, and <er>Pollard</er>.]</ety> <def>An upright wooden
or iron post in a boat or on a dock, used in veering or fastening
ropes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bollard timber</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a
timber, also called a <xex>knighthead</xex>, rising just within the stem
in a ship, on either side of the bowsprit, to secure its
end.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bollen</ent>⟦br⟧
